President Obama had a meeting with his national security team to discuss Afghanistan and Pakistan. He was updated on our engagement with the Pakistani Government, including efforts to strengthen cooperation along the Afghanistan-Pakistan border. The President also received an update on Afghanistan, focusing on building Afghan security forces, supporting an Afghan-led reconciliation process, and establishing a long-term strategic partnership between the US and Afghanistan. Additionally, preparations for the NATO Summit in Chicago were discussed, where the ongoing transition to Afghan-led security and NATO's commitment to the future of Afghanistan will be defined.